raw_data.title: Engagement Management
raw_data.description: The position oversees projects to ensure client satisfaction and success. Key responsibilities include acting as a primary point of contact, managing projects, collecting feedback, and driving retention or motivation strategies. The specific duties vary based on clients, employees, project.

raw_data.title: Project Management/Business Analyst
raw_data.description: The position defines and documents business needs, translates them into detailed requirements, and ensures that the solution delivers value and aligns with strategic goals. Key responsibilities include conducting gap analysis and feasibility studies, creating process maps, writing user stories, and acting as a liaison between stakeholders and the development team to facilitate communication and achieve project success.

raw_data.title: Jr. Devops Engineer
raw_data.description: Performs support for development and operations teams by automating processes, managing infrastructure, and ensuring software reliability through CI/CD pipelines. Responsibilities include setting up servers, managing cloud resources, monitoring system performance, and resolving technical issues, often using scripting and DevOps tools. Key requirements are foundational knowledge in coding, cloud platforms, and system administration, along with strong problem-solving and communication skills

raw_data.title: Sr. Developer
raw_data.description: An experienced professional responsible for leading the design, development, and maintenance of complex software applications. Key responsibilities include writing high-quality code, conducting code reviews, troubleshooting complex issues, and making strategic architectural decisions. Sr. Developers collaborate with cross-functional teams and stay updated on emerging technologies to drive project success and foster innovation.

raw_data.title: Sr. Quality Assurance Testing
raw_data.description: Position leads testing efforts, designing and executing complex test strategies, mentoring junior team members, automating tests, analyzing results, driving defect resolution, improving processes, and ensuring compliance with quality standards for software development. Key responsibilities involve collaborating with cross-functional teams, developing test plans, performing root cause analysis, and communicating results to stakeholders to ensure high-quality software delivery.

raw_data.title: User Experience Design
raw_data.description: The position involves ensuring a product is user-friendly, efficient, and enjoyable by conducting user research, creating wireframes and prototypes, and performing usability testing. They collaborate with cross-functional teams, including product managers, developers, and UI designers, to understand user needs and business goals to create intuitive and accessible user experiences for digital products like websites and apps. Key skills include problem-solving, and proficiency in design tools to advocate for the user throughout the product development process.

raw_data.title: Healthcare Sr. Project Analyst
raw_data.description: A Sr. Project Analyst analyzes project data to develop strategies, supports project planning and execution, and focuses on areas like electronic health records, data analysis, and business process improvement to ensure project success and optimize operations within a healthcare setting.

raw_data.title: Healthcaer Sr. Devops Engineer
raw_data.description: A Sr. DevOps engineer leads the design, development, and implementation of the DevOps strategy to accelerate software delivery and improve system reliability, bridging the gap between development and operations teams. They automate software testing, deployment, and infrastructure using tools like Terraform and Git, manage CI/CD pipelines, and oversee cloud infrastructure and monitoring. Senior engineers manage incidents, ensure system security, and make critical decisions to optimize performance and align technical efforts with business goals.

raw_data.title: Healthcare Software Architect
raw_data.description: Software Architects design, develop, and oversee robust, scalable, and secure software systems for healthcare organizations, ensuring they meet business objectives, clinical workflows, and regulatory standards. Key responsibilities include creating system architectures, integrating legacy and modern systems, leveraging advanced technologies like AI and cloud-native approaches, collaborating with cross-functional teams, and mentoring engineers.

raw_data.title: Healthcare Jr. Developer
raw_data.description: Position creates, tests, and maintains software for hospitals and clinics, often focusing on Electronic Health Records (EHR), patient management, or medical billing systems. Key responsibilities include writing and debugging code, ensuring software compliance with regulations like HIPAA, and collaborating with senior developers and healthcare professionals to deliver user-friendly, secure, and effective digital tools.

raw_data.title: Healthcare Jr. Quality Assurance Testing
raw_data.description: Jr. Quality Assurance Testers ensure healthcare software is reliable, functional, and compliant with regulations like HIPAA by designing, executing tests, and documenting defects for healthcare applications such as EHRs. This role involves learning to create and run test cases, potentially some automation, tracking bugs, and collaborating with teams to improve product quality.

raw_data.title: Healthcare Graphic Design
raw_data.description: Graphic Designers create visual materials like infographics, website graphics, and branding for hospitals and healthcare organizations to communicate complex health information clearly to diverse audiences. Key responsibilities include collaborating with medical professionals and marketing teams, ensuring accuracy and compliance with healthcare regulations, and designing engaging, accessible content for both print and digital platforms. The role demands a strong understanding of design principles, medical terminology, and accessibility standards.
